25/09/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Another wave of torrential rains and flooding struck on Thursday (September 24th), claiming five lives in the northeast province of Artvin, near the border with Georgia and Armenia. 
Several other people are missing. 
Rescue operations supported by the army continue in the region. 
Earlier this month, flash floods caused by heavy rains killed 37 people in the northwestern Istanbul and Tekirdag provinces. 
(Turkiye, Zaman - 25/09/09; BBC, Anadolu news agency, Xinhua - 24/09/09)
